        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-07-24 11:04:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> I think it is needed to invoke the script with 3 arguments: username, password, and host, as they may change from installation to installation.   For example, policydb will not be valid when working in a csit environment.\n\nI think you are saying is to make this script configurable for all 3 inputs? Which could be overridden depending on environment (eg local dev, CSIT, k8s, etc.)",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
